               <!-- Start_Module_13623 -->
               <div id="dnn_ctr13623_ModuleContent" class="DNNModuleContent ModDNNHTMLC">
                  <div id="dnn_ctr13623_HtmlModule_lblContent">
                     <h2>What currency is used in China?</h2>
                     <p>In China, the legal tender is CNY (Chinese Yuan), also known as RMB (Renminbi).</p>
                     <p>Notes are issued to the value of ¥100, ¥50, ¥20, ¥10, ¥5 and ¥1. Coins are used less frequently in the North of China.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
